A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a Singapore classroom where young students in uniforms gather around a large, glowing futuristic holographic display floating above an old wooden teacher's desk. The contrast between traditional wooden chairs, chalkboards with chalk dust, and the ethereal blue-green digital projection creates visual tension. Through large colonial-era windows, tropical trees are visible. The students' faces are illuminated by the soft glow, expressions full of wonder and curiosity. Warm sepia and amber tones dominate the scene with cool cyan accents from the technology. The composition uses dramatic perspective, looking up slightly at the floating display, giving it an aspirational quality. Rendered in a nostalgic mid-century educational poster aesthetic with visible grain texture and slightly faded colors at the edges.
